# Stripe Billing Kit — Cursor Rules

## 开始任何 Stripe 相关代码工作前，先加载官方文档上下文

```bash
npx skills add https://docs.stripe.com
/plugin install stripe@claude-plugins-official
```

## 本项目核心规则

You are working on **stripe-billing-kit** — a framework-agnostic, plug-and-play Stripe billing integration kit.

### Architecture
- `packages/core/` — Framework-agnostic core (TypeScript). All billing logic lives here.
- `packages/adapter-next/` — Next.js App Router adapter
- `packages/adapter-express/` — Express adapter
- `packages/react/` — React components + hooks
- `packages/vue/` — Vue 3 components + composables
- `packages/electron/` — Electron desktop integration
- `docs/` — All integration guides. READ THESE FIRST.
- `templates/` — Config templates and DB schemas

### Coding Rules
1. **Never hardcode price IDs** — always use `lookup_key` via `getCatalog()`, or reference `plan.ref.priceId` from config
2. **Never accept priceId from frontend** — frontend sends `planKey` only; server resolves to priceId
3. **Webhook signature must be verified** — use `stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()` with raw body
4. **Deduplicate webhooks by event.id** — check `billing_events` table before processing
5. **`syncStripeToDb()` is the only source of truth** — never write subscription state directly; always call sync
6. **`BillingConfig` drives all SDK calls** — create context with `createBillingContext(config)`
7. **All 7 plan types are implemented** — see `packages/core/src/checkout.ts` for switch cases

### 8 Supported Plan Types
- `subscription` — recurring monthly/yearly
- `daily` — single-day pass (non-recurring)
- `credit_package` — one-time credit bundle
- `metered` — usage-based (Stripe Meter)
- `trial_then_subscribe` — trial with card, auto-converts
- `trial_no_convert` — trial without card, expires
- `one_time` — lifetime/one-time purchase
- `first_trial` — new user exclusive first trial (one-time only)

### Key API Patterns
```ts
// 1. Create billing context (singleton per config)
const ctx = createBillingContext(billingConfig);

// 2. Create checkout session (supports all 7 plan types)
const { url } = await createCheckoutSession(ctx, { userId, planKey });

// 3. Handle webhooks
const event = await handleWebhook(ctx, rawBody, signature);

// 4. Check entitlements
const { hasAccess, features } = await checkEntitlement(ctx, userId, 'feature-name');

// 5. Report metered usage
await reportUsage(ctx, { userId, planKey, quantity: 5 });
```

### Stripe SDK Version
Always use stripe-node `^17.x`. Verify API shapes at https://stripe.com/docs/api

### Testing Cards
- Success: `4242 4242 4242 4242`
- 3DS required: `4000 0025 0000 3155`
- Insufficient funds: `4000 0000 0000 9995`
- Declined: `4000 0000 0000 0002`

All cards: future expiry date, any 3-digit CVV, zip `42424`

